version: 1
display_name: PHTN-50-000208 - The Photon operating system must configure Secure Shell (SSH) to disable user environment processing.
global_description: |-
  Enabling user environment processing may enable users to bypass access restrictions in some configurations and must therefore be disabled.
osfinger:
  - VMware Photon OS-5
refs:
  disa_stig:
    - PHTN-50-000208
  srg:
    - SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00229
  cci:
    - CCI-000366
  nist:
    - CM-6 b
benchmark_id:
  vcf9_photon_5:
    type: custom
    desc: The Photon operating system must configure Secure Shell (SSH) to disable user environment processing.
    control_id: PHTN-50-000208
    scored: true
    profile:
      - default
    information: |-
      At the command line, run the following command to verify the running configuration of sshd:

      # sshd -T|&grep -i PermitUserEnvironment

      Example result:

      permituserenvironment no

      If "PermitUserEnvironment" is not set to "no", this is a finding.
    rationale: |-
      Enabling user environment processing may enable users to bypass access restrictions in some configurations and must therefore be disabled.
    remediation: |-
      Navigate to and open:

      /etc/ssh/sshd_config

      Ensure the "PermitUserEnvironment" line is uncommented and set to the following:

      PermitUserEnvironment no

      At the command line, run the following command:

      # systemctl restart sshd.service
